article.headline: Colorado rolls to seventh victory in a row
article.linkText: No. 25 Buffaloes just too much for Buffalo
article.story:
AMHERST, N.Y. (AP) -- Kate Fagan and Randie Wirt each scored 15
points as Colorado beat Buffalo 76-47 Thursday night for its
seventh consecutive victory.

	   Colorado (10-1) took control from the opening tip, scoring the
first nine points. The Buffaloes led 25-6 with 6:51 to go in the
first half and 37-14 at halftime.

	   Buffalo (7-2) had its five-game winning streak snapped.

	   Sabrina Scott and Tera Bjorklund each had 11 points, and
Veronica Johns-Richardson added 10 points and a career-high four
steals for Colorado.

	   Wirt's layup with 9:50 left gave Colorado its biggest lead,
59-27.

	   Kate McMeeken-Ruscoe led Buffalo with 15 points. Allison Bennett
and Kim Kilpela had 10 points apiece.

	   Colorado shot 44.4 percent from the field in the first half and
forced 14 turnovers. Buffalo shot just 25.9 percent for the half.
